parties.raw_snippet:
THIS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is dated as of June 11, 2015, by and between Marathon Petroleum
Company LP (“Shipper”) and Marathon Pipe Line LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“MPL”), both referred to jointly as the “Parties” and each
individually as a “Party”.
parties.reasoning: The opening paragraph explicitly names the two contracting parties by their legal names.

contract_type.reasoning: The agreement’s title and substance describe pipeline transportation services with volume commitments and tariff rates.

notice_period.raw_snippet: This Agreement will automatically renew for up to two (2) renewal terms of five (5) years each (each, an “Extension Period”) unless either Party provides the other Party with written notice of its intent to terminate this Agreement at least six (6) months prior to the end of the Initial Term or the then current Extension Period.
notice_period.reasoning: Section 2.2 sets an automatic renewal and specifies the advance written notice required to prevent renewal.

expiration_date.raw_snippet:
The Agreement shall continue through the project’s in-service date and
for a period of fifteen (15) years after the project’s in-service date (“Initial Term”).
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 2.1 defines a relative term measured from the project’s in-service date rather than a specific calendar date.
expiration_date.normalized_value: 15 years after the project's in-service date

renewal_term.raw_snippet: This Agreement will automatically renew for up to two (2) renewal terms of five (5) years each (each, an “Extension Period”)
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 2.2 states the automatic renewal structure and length of each renewal term.
